---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<head>
  <title>Tools for Collective Action — BoycottWithAI</title>
  <meta name="description" content="Templates, event planners, and privacy-first coordination tools for non-violent campaigns. Start with a 4-step plan." />
</head>

<Base>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="left">
      <h1>Tools for Collective Action</h1>
  <p class="lead">A curated set of practical tools to organize, coordinate, and amplify collective actions. These tools are structured to support the phases of a strategic campaign: awareness, mobilization, escalation, and sustaining pressure.</p>
      <div class="cta">
        <a class="button" href="/actions/">Explore Actions</a>
        <a class="secondary" href="/map/">Open Map</a>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="card" style="width:420px">
  <h3>Quick tools</h3>
  <ul>
  <li><strong>Event Planner</strong> — Plan assemblies that prioritize accessibility, legal observers, and escalation paths.</li>
    <li><strong>Secure Messaging</strong> — Guidance for encrypted coordination and privacy-preserving communications.</li>
    <li><strong>Contact Templates</strong> — Scripts for outreach to companies, partners, and media to apply coordinated pressure.</li>
  </ul>
      <hr />
  <p class="muted">Use these components to build campaigns that scale responsibly: plan phases, assign roles, and monitor success metrics like participation rate and media reach.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section style="margin-top:28px">
    <div class="grid">
      <div class="card">
        <h4>Mobilization Kits</h4>
  <p>Bundled resources: posters, chant sheets, accessibility guides, legal observers checklist. Downloadable templates help you move quickly from plan to action.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h4>Digital Actions</h4>
  <p>How to run coordinated social media pushes, hashtag campaigns, and doxx-resistant outreach. Tools to measure reach (demo analytics).</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h4>Training</h4>
  <p>Short modules: de-escalation, affinity group formation, first aid basics, legal rights. Link to open-source curricula (example links).</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section style="margin-top:20px">
    <div class="card">
      <h4>How to Start (4 steps)</h4>
      <ol>
        <li>Define objective and target (who holds the leverage).</li>
        <li>Build a coalition and map roles (communications, legal, medics).</li>
        <li>Run a pilot action and measure results (participation, reach).</li>
        <li>Scale using phased escalation and accountability metrics.</li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
